<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-02-15T23:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-02-15T23:36:00-05:00" n="816" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d816">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/6177.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Ambassador</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams—Paraphrases.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-02-15T22:00:00-06:36">
                                    <hi rend="italic">February 15, 1913—10 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Please call the attention of the President to the circumstance that the
                            Associated Press has brought a [rumor?] to Mexico that the President has
                            stated that he would intervene in Mexico only after a wanton slaughter
                            of Americans. The Mexican Herald suppressed this telegram, but President
                            Madero used it today in connection with his arguments why he should not
                            resign.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>